text: Golden Valley County is a county in the U.S. state of North Dakota. As of the 2020 census, there were 1,736 people living there, making it the fourth-least populous county in North Dakota. The county seat is Beach. The county is not be confused with the city of Golden Valley, in Mercer County. == References == Category:1912 establishments in the United States Category:20th-century establishments in North Dakota Category:North Dakota counties
